Omololu Ogunmade in Abuja and Francis Sardauna in Katsina President Muhammadu Buhari and Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State have expressed sadness over the death of a former Inspector General of Police (IG) and Chairman of Arewa Consultative Forum (ACF), Alhaji Ibrahim Ahmadu Coomassie. The younger brother of the deceased Dahiru Commassie, who confirmed the new thursday in Katsina, said the former IG died thrsday evening at the age of 76 years. THISDAY gathered that Coomassie, who held the traditional title of Sardaunan-Katsina, was rushed to the Orthopedic Hospital in Katsina around 11a.m. yesterday morning for an undisclosed ailment but regained his consciousness after an hour and gave up around 5p.m.
The corpse of the former boss chief was said to have been brought to his residence from the hospital where he died. Information from family members, however, indicated that Coomassie’s funeral rites would be performed today after Jumaat prayers at his mosque in GRA, a stone throw from his residence. The deceased was survived with one wife, six children and many grandchildren.
Masari lamented that the death of the former IG was a loss to Nigeria. He said the former IG was one of the last standing patriots who served the nation with distinction.
President Buhari on his part, commiserated with the family members, the government and people of Katsina State the demise of the former IG whom he described as his classmate. The president, according Malam Garba Shehu, said he received the news of the death of the Chairman of ACF with shock and deep sense of loss. “Nigeria will never forget the excellent leadership the late Coomassie gave to the Nigeria PPolice Force for the many years he served as IG,” the president said